reviewText: I bought this album for David Phelp's 'No More Night.'  I had heard it all before, and did so much want to have the first song I ever heard David sing solo.  However, I now enjoy most of the whole thing. Some of my friends love it. I am not sorry I bought it. It is different than the others, and therefore a treasure also, because some of the music is very pretty indeed.Mickey

reviewText: I have enjoyed the amazing Gaither's gospel music on television channels for many years and it is a great family tradition and worship. The voices of the Home Coming group blend in so well that the music hall is filled with inspiration and love rendered in praising the lord. It is a music ministry of faith, hope, peace and harmony.Some of my favorite songs from this DVD are; "Beautiful Isle of Somewhere," "One Day" and "Canaan land is Just in Sight." This performance includes the works of; Amber Thompson, Buddy Greene, Stephen Hill, Tanya Goodman Sykes, Squire Parsons, Bobbie Mason, Woody Wright, Janet Paschal and the gospel family of Bill and Gloria Gaither.1.Bill Gaither's 20 All-Time  Favorite Homecoming Songs and Performances, Vol. 22.Bill Gaither's 20 All-Time Favorite Homecoming Songs & Performances, Vol. 13.Bill & Gloria Gaither: The Old Rugged Cross4.Gaither Homecoming Celebration!
summary: Amazing voices of Bill Gaither's Home Coming singers
